First Lady Melania Trump and Tennessee Governor Bill Lee held a call to discuss children's well-being and Tennessee's efforts to address mental and physical health for children and families. Governor Lee discussed the creation of the state's COVID-19 Child Wellbeing Task Force, which focuses on whole child care, including mental and physical health. They emphasized the importance of ensuring the well-being of all children, including minority children who may face additional barriers to care. Tennessee is working to reduce barriers and using COVID-19 testing sites to connect communities in need with critical social services. They also discussed innovative ways to care for children with disabilities during the pandemic.